text: Rio Grande County is a county in the state of Colorado in the United States. As of the 2020 census, 11,539 people lived there. The county seat is Del Norte. The county is named for the Rio Grande (Spanish language for "Big River"), which flows through the county. ==References== Category:Colorado counties Category:1870s establishments in Colorado Territory Category:1874 establishments in the United States
title: Rio Grande County, Colorado
